---
title: Make-Ahead Cheesy Bacon Biscuit Bombs 3x the delicious servings!
description: We’re serving up all your favorite breakfast flavors in a flaky buttermilk biscuit! These loaded bacon and cheese biscuit bombs are super-easy to make ahead and have onhand for busy mornings, snacks, or even to pack for school or work. You’ll simply roll out biscuit dough, top with a creamy, garlicky filling of cheddar, Monterey Jack, cream cheese, and crispy bacon, then roll 'em up into balls, and bake until golden brown and puffed. You can serve these crowd-pleasers right away with a luscious side of scallion butter, or stash in the fridge until you’re ready to reheat.

Make Ahead Breakfast: This recipe is triple the typical servings, providing 6 servings and 12 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64f8892ef6dcf759f5e610ef-95a25a7b.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64f8892ef6dcf759f5e610ef.pdf
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/make-ahead-cheesy-bacon-biscuit-bombs-64f8892ef6dcf759f5e610ef
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 45 minutes
author: Sara Heilman
